  "StockRole": "Ultralight FlameMech",
  "YangsThoughts": "The Foxfire is the brainchild of Karl von der Burg, a senior engineer with Defiance Industries. Inspired by flamethrower tanks used during the Second World War on Terra his goal became to create a highly mobile armored platform to deliver devastating overheating attacks on other 'Mechs. When first fielded, battlefield commanders were not sure of the role for such a 'Mech, which meant the Foxfire was usually put to use as a very mobile scout unit. However, once the strength of specialized incendiary lances was realized, the 'Mech quickly became a great success and quite a fearful target. As more modern cooling technology is being discovered, the heat from a few flamers do not pose such a large threat anymore and the Foxfire once again started falling back to its old scouting role.",
